annotationA: Spaghetti squash (sqh) is the regulatory light chain of the nonmuscle type 2 myosin. Its phosphorylation through the Rho-Rho Kinase pathway is predicted to activate myosin motor activity. Sqh and myosin function in cellular processes such as cytokinesis, and also contribute to tissue morphogenesis
annotationB: Dreadlocks, isoform B; SH3/SH2 adaptor activity; protein binding; insulin receptor binding; cell adhesion molecule binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: myoblast fusion; axonogenesis; insulin receptor signaling pathway; negative regulation of insulin receptor signaling pathway; axon guidance
